com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.documents

Interface Renamable

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultAlignmentDocument, DefaultAminoAcidSequence, DefaultNucleotideGraphSequence, DefaultNucleotideSequence, DefaultPhylogenyDocument, DefaultSequenceDocument, DefaultSequenceListDocument, OligoSequenceDocument, PhylogenyDocument

    public interface Renamable
    Provides that ability to rename something. This is intended to be implemented by PluginDocuments to allow changing the name returned from PluginDocument.getName().

    For most PluginDocuments this is unncessary, because the getName() implementation is automatically overridden when it is wrapped inside an AnnotatedPluginDocument. But for documents that appear wrapped inside a collection (e.g. a SequenceListDocument) the getName() implementation is not overridable by the AnnotatedPluginDocument, and setting the name via this Renamable interface is useful.
